<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>26-908</num>
  <heading>Fees allowed on foreclosure.</heading>
  <text>In any foreclosure on any loan made under this chapter no charges for attorneys’ or agents’ fees shall be made or collected which will exceed 10% of the amount found due in such foreclosure proceedings.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 62-3-ch26" path="§8">Feb. 4, 1913, 37 Stat. 660, ch. 26, § 8</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 26-608.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 26-708.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
